cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a vision-based vehicle recognition method. Additionally, the use of fuzzy rules and reasoning system suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The application of the method in road traffic control and surveillance systems suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of image data and segmentation techniques suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
